(150, 4, 'Dear Hanna,<br><br>How are you? I really miss you. I havent written a letter to you for a long time, because I am very busy. I am so sorry for that. <br><br>I have been studying in the English Language Center at BYU in Provo, Utah. I have been here since January 2017 (Kurikulum 2013). This is a famous university. It is very beautiful. This university has a lot of good lecturers and good disciplines. I have learned a lot from the university; every day I have a lot of homework I need to do, and every week I have many tests. Sometimes I feel very tired, and I want to have a rest for a few days but I cant do that. <br><br>Do you know why I dont study in New York? You know, in New York, there are many Chinese; I can use Chinese as I have learned it since I was born. It is like living in China. I wont study English well in New York. Provo is a school city. There are many universities here. People here are very kind and polite. I have made many American friends here. Provo also has a beautiful view in winter; there are a lot of white, snow-covered mountains. It is so beautiful. I love it very much. Sometimes I go skiing with my friends. <br><br>Although everything is good here, I still have some problems. My husband and my son are in New York. I am very worried about them. Every Sunday I go to the church to pray to God. I want God help me take care of them. The other problem is the food here is not good for me, but it is okay.<br><br>How about you and your study? Please tell me when you write a letter to me.<br><br><br><br>Love,<br><br>Rachma<br><br>I want God help me <u>take care </u>of them. (Paragraph 4)<br>What is the synonym of the underlined word?', 'Cope with.', 'Look after.', 'Deal to.', 'Bring about.', 'b', ''),
